# session/tooling scratch at repo root — machine-local, never committed
.agents/skills/
# `.reports/*` (not `.reports/`) — git CANNOT re-include a path under an EXCLUDED DIRECTORY, so the
# directory itself must stay walkable for the negation below to work at all.
.reports/*
# ── Cycle 7: `.reports/architecture/` IS TRACKED. ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# It was ignored as "session scratch", which meant the ENTIRE architectural knowledge base — the
# manifest, the KB, the implementation contract, every canonical artifact of Cycles 1-6 — WAS NOT
# IN THE REPOSITORY. Consequences, all of them fatal to governance:
#   * CI never saw it, so an architecture gate would have found no inputs and PASSED VACUOUSLY —
#     a green check that checks nothing, which is worse than no check at all;
#   * "regenerate and byte-compare against the committed artifacts" compares against NOTHING;
#   * the "architectural authority" lived on ONE developer's disk and died with the machine.
# It is text (~1.9 MB of .md + .json) and it is now load-bearing: `python -m tools.arch ci` reads it,
# and rule GOV-001 FAILS LOUDLY if it is absent rather than skipping the checks that need it.
!.reports/architecture/
.codemap-cache/
.codemap-cache-test/
skills-lock.json
